This paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) tasks and proposes a compression method for deep learning models used in text classification. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves matrix factorization, which is a common technique in machine learning and falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper proposes a novel learning rate schedule, which is a popular topic in the field of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also involves analyzing the inference time and storage space, which are common topics in computer vision (cs.CV) and neural networks (cs.NE).
